# Creating RDDs & SparkContext

## Two doors into Spark

- **`spark`** (SparkSession) — the high-level door: DataFrames, SQL
- **`sc`** (SparkContext) — the low-level door: RDDs, broadcasts, accumulators
- Grab it with `spark.sparkContext` — same JVM, same cluster

## Where an RDD comes from

- **`sc.parallelize(seq)`** — distribute a driver list (tests/demos)
- **`sc.range(start, end)`** — an RDD of longs, no Python list
- **`sc.textFile(path)`** — one element per line
- **`sc.wholeTextFiles(path)`** — `(filename, content)` per small file
- **`df.rdd`** — drop to a DataFrame's underlying `Row` RDD

Most RDDs, in practice, are born from **transformations** on other RDDs.
